<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2024-03-20T13:22:22.712Z" lasteditedby="44785" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Gear Module</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Gear<keyword>Circular Pitch</keyword><keyword>Module</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Circular Pitch</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> is the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">circumference of gear / number of teeth</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Circular Pitch: <equation style="vertical-align:baseline;vertical-align:text-bottom" font-size="22" color="#000000">P=\lfrac{\pi.d}{N}</equation></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Gear Module</text> is the metric size, in millimeters(<text style="font-size:9pt;">mm</text>), of a gear-tooth<text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">To get <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Module</text>, we drop the irrational number, <equation font-size="24">\pi</equation>, from <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Circular Pitch.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px;"><equation styleclass="VariableName-small">\therefore</equation><text styleclass="VariableName-small"> Gear Module:</text> <equation style="vertical-align:baseline;vertical-align:text-bottom">m=\lfrac{P}{\pi}\ \ = \ \ \lfrac{d}{N}</equation></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">or, Gear Module(</text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="font-size:9pt;">mm</text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">) = P.C.D. ∕ number-of-teeth</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:15px;">Units of <text styleclass="VariableName-small">module</text> are <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="font-size:9pt;">mm</text>, but they are usually omitted.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Gear-Module-Standard">Industry Standard Modules</link></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Gear-PCD">P.C.D. Pitch-Circle-Diameter - definition</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
